sequenceDiagram
    actor U as Exclusive User
    participant FE as React<br/>AttackChainPage
    participant API1 as DRF<br/>AttackChainListView
    participant API2 as DRF<br/>AttackChainDetailView
    participant SER as AttackChainDetailSerializer
    participant Perm as IsExclusiveOrAbove
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    U->>FE: Navigate to Attack Chains page
    FE->>API1: GET /api/attack-chains/
    API1->>Perm: has_permission(request)
    Perm-->>API1: Allowed (Exclusive tier)
    API1->>DB: AttackChain.objects.filter(environment=env)
    DB-->>API1: QuerySet[AttackChain]
    API1-->>FE: 200 OK {chains: [...]}
    FE->>FE: AttackChainCard(chain) for each
    FE-->>U: Display attack chain timeline cards
    U->>FE: Click chain for details
    FE->>API2: GET /api/attack-chains/{id}/
    API2->>DB: AttackChain.objects.get(pk=id)
    DB-->>API2: Chain with linked alerts
    API2->>SER: AttackChainDetailSerializer(chain)
    SER-->>API2: Full chain data with alert nodes
    API2-->>FE: 200 OK {chain detail with phases}
    FE->>FE: getPhase(technique) for MITRE mapping
    FE->>FE: AlertNode(alert) for each alert in chain
    FE-->>U: Display kill chain visualization with alert nodes
